# 15 : MLIR — CSSLv3-MIR as MLIR-dialect
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ THESIS
  CSSLv3-MIR = MLIR-dialect from-day-one (R6)
  reuse : Linalg + Affine + Transform + SCF + Vector + GPU + SPIR-V dialects
  own : cssl-dialect for domain-specific ops
  ≡ 10-years of MLIR passes usable-for-free

§ LINEAGE
  LLVM/MLIR project (Lattner et al. 2019+)
  IREE : ML-compilation with MLIR (Google, Apache-2)
  Mojo : Python-superset on MLIR (Modular)
  Triton : GPU-kernels via MLIR (OpenAI)
  CIRCT : hardware-design with MLIR
  we adopt : dialect-pattern + Transform-dialect for staging

§ CSSL-DIALECT OPS (custom)
  cssl.diff.primal     @differentiable fn primal-variant
  cssl.diff.fwd        forward-mode derivative
  cssl.diff.bwd        reverse-mode derivative
  cssl.jet.construct   build Jet<T, N>
  cssl.jet.project     extract Nth Taylor-term
  cssl.effect.perform  invoke operation of effect
  cssl.effect.handle   install effect-handler
  cssl.region.enter    start region-scope
  cssl.region.exit     end region-scope (free arena)
  cssl.handle.pack     construct Handle<T> from (idx, gen)
  cssl.handle.unpack   extract (idx, gen)
  cssl.handle.check    generation-validate
  cssl.staged.splice   @staged expansion-site
  cssl.staged.quote    AST-value in staged-context
  cssl.staged.run      #run comptime-eval
  cssl.macro.expand    tier-1/2 macro-expansion point
  cssl.ifc.label       attach IFC-label to SSA-value
  cssl.ifc.declassify  explicit declassification
  cssl.verify.assert   SMT-obligation (§§ 20)
  cssl.sdf.march       ray-march SDF'L<k≤1>
  cssl.sdf.normal      bwd_diff-based normal
  cssl.gpu.barrier     memory-barrier
  cssl.gpu.subgroup.*  subgroup ops (shuffle, vote, arith)
  cssl.xmx.coop_matmul cooperative-matrix multiply
  cssl.rt.trace_ray    ray-tracing dispatch
  cssl.rt.intersect    custom-intersection-shader
  cssl.telemetry.probe<scope>  R18 probe-point

§ REUSED MLIR DIALECTS
  arith      integer + float arithmetic
  scf        structured control-flow (scf.if, scf.for, scf.while)
  cf         generic CFG (used rarely — we prefer scf)
  func       function definitions + calls
  memref     memory-reference (CPU-side buffers)
  vector     fixed-width vector ops (SIMD)
  tensor     multi-dim arrays
  linalg     structured linear-algebra (matmul, conv, reduce)
  affine     affine-loop-nests (polyhedral opt)
  gpu        generic-GPU (thread-id, barrier, device-mem)
  spirv      SPIR-V 1-to-1 ops
  llvm       LLVM-dialect (we use subset for Cranelift bridge stage0)
  transform  programmable pass-schedules (F4 × MLIR)

§ TRANSFORM-DIALECT (F4 × R9 host-layer)
  Transform-dialect from upstream MLIR expresses pass-schedules as-IR
  CSSLv3 @staged specializer emits transform-ops :
    transform.structured.tile   — loop-tiling with sizes
    transform.structured.fuse   — loop-fusion
    transform.gpu.map_parallel  — GPU-kernel-mapping
    transform.interpreter       — runs transform-schedule on target-IR
  @staged-call → transform-schedule → rewrites target-IR
  ≡ staging becomes first-class IR-to-IR transformation
  ≡ Futamura-P1 realized as Transform-dialect program

§ STRUCTURED CFG PRESERVATION (CC4)
  cssl + scf dialects used exclusively for control-flow
  NO cf.br / cf.cond_br (unstructured) emitted from CSSLv3-source
  compile-time rejection of unstructured-patterns
  lowering to spirv-dialect preserves scf → OpSelectionMerge / OpLoopMerge
  lowering to llvm-dialect (Cranelift stage0) decomposes scf → structured CLIF
  ‼ canonical validator @ `cssl_mir::structured_cfg::validate_structured_cfg` :
    see specs/02_IR.csl § STRUCTURED-CFG VALIDATOR for the diagnostic-code
    table (CFG0001..CFG0010) + marker-contract + pipeline-position.

§ PASS-PIPELINE (MIR → LIR)
  1 : cssl-to-cssl
      monomorphization
      macro-expansion (cssl.macro.expand → expanded ops)
      @staged-specializer (transform-dialect driven)
      AD source-transform (cssl.diff.* → expanded fwd/bwd ops)
      Jet expansion (cssl.jet.* → tuple-of-tangent ops)
      evidence-passing (cssl.effect.* → plain values + fn-calls)
      IFC-propagation + declassification-validate
      SMT-discharge (cssl.verify.assert → proof-obligations)
      telemetry-probe insertion (cssl.telemetry.probe<scope>)
      structured-CFG validate + region-lifetime check
  2 : cssl-to-standard
      cssl.region → memref.alloca + memref.dealloc
      cssl.handle → arith + memref ops
      cssl.sdf.march → scf.while + func.call
      cssl.gpu.* → gpu.*
      cssl.xmx.* → spirv cooperative-matrix ops
      cssl.rt.* → spirv ray-tracing ops
      remaining cssl.* → standard ops where-possible
  3 : standard-optimization
      canonicalization
      cse (common-subexpression elimination)
      loop-invariant-code-motion (LICM)
      dead-code-elimination (DCE)
      inliner (with effect-row-preserving inlining)
      linalg-fusion (when linalg dialect used)
      affine-opt (when affine dialect used)
  4 : dialect-conversion to-target
      spirv-dialect → rspirv builder (stage0) | owned emitter (stage1+)
      llvm-dialect subset → Cranelift bridge (stage0)
      cssl-owned-lowering → own-backend (stage1+)

§ DIALECT DEFINITION (TableGen stage0)
  include/cssl/Dialect/CSSL/IR/CSSLOps.td
  each op :
    name : "cssl.diff.primal"
    operands : variadic<AnyType>
    results  : variadic<AnyType>
    attributes : ifc_label, cap, effect_row, source_loc
    traits : Pure | HasEffects<...> | AlwaysSpeculatable | ...
    verifiers : op-specific invariants
    printer / parser : textual-MLIR format
    canonicalization patterns : tblgen or C++ handwritten
  stage1+ : same in CSSLv3-native attribute-definition

§ INTEROP WITH EXTERNAL MLIR PROJECTS
  IREE : possible-future-integration for ML-workload offload
  Triton : not-integrated (we emit own GPU-kernels)
  CIRCT : future FPGA-target via CIRCT dialects
  Polygeist : not-used (C-to-MLIR bridge not-relevant)

§ COMPILE-TIME OVERHEAD
  stage0 with MLIR : ~200ms per-module fixed cost + per-op cost
  acceptable for dev-loop (2s incremental target still met)
  stage1+ : may strip MLIR-infrastructure if not-needed beyond staging
  alternative stage1 path : emit custom-IR skipping MLIR (opt-in)
    trade : lose Transform-dialect, gain ~50ms per-module

§ DIAGNOSTIC + DEBUGGING
  MLIR textual-format : human-readable IR dumps
  --emit-mlir flag : dump IR at-each-pass
  --dump-pass=<name> : isolate specific pass output
  source-map preserved through all passes
  error-messages reference CSSLv3 source-line via srcloc-attribute

§ PROS vs CONS (addressed)
  PRO : 10y of upstream passes reusable (linalg, affine, Transform, etc)
  PRO : dialect-pattern is well-suited to CSSLv3's multi-abstraction layers
  PRO : Transform-dialect ≡ F4-staging infrastructure
  CON : C++ template-heavy (mitigated by Rust mlir-sys + melior bindings)
  CON : docs-sparse (mitigated by stage1+ custom dialect in CSSLv3-native)
  CON : compile-time-overhead (acceptable + has-escape-hatch)

∎ MLIR
